<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3442] @Singleton doesn&apos;t support getInstance() as documented</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3442</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;e.g.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Singleton &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;MyService{
}

println MyService.instance &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// it works as expected
&lt;/span&gt;println MyService.getInstance() &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; exception: No signature of method: &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; MyService.getInstance() is applicable &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; argument types: () values: []&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;p.s. i found an old issue about Singleton in Groovy that probably could be closed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1870&quot; title=&quot;Add support for singleton pattern&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-1870&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-1870&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
