                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14466734" author="roshandawrani" created="Mon, 30 Mar 2009 12:16:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the non-lazy variation of @Singleton, the getInstance() was not being added. Only &quot;instance&quot; was being added as a public property. So, getInstance() call was failing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch that adds property as private and its getInstance() &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;same as lazy variant of @Singleton&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let me know if it looks ok.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466711" author="roshandawrani" created="Sat, 4 Apr 2009 01:08:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any review comments on the patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466903" author="blackdrag" created="Mon, 6 Apr 2009 06:37:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Roshan, I think it is no problem if there is a public field and the getter. In the non lazy case the getter should simply return the field, without any further checks. So I would remove the null check from the patch. In &lt;a href=&quot;http://markmail.org/message/ykofpk4yepuwoinf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://markmail.org/message/ykofpk4yepuwoinf&lt;/a&gt; I suggested the use of a final static property and I still think that is the way to go for the non lazy variant.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466905" author="roshandawrani" created="Mon, 6 Apr 2009 10:13:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed. Added the getter getInstance() for non-lazy variant of Singleton annotation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
